CONTEXT NODE

context_node is the citizen who holds the running state of an ongoing conversation
when input_node forwards a new sentence, context_node integrates it with what has been said before
context_node remembers who is speaking, what tone has been set, what topics have come up, and where the conversation is at this moment
without context_node, every exchange would feel like fadriel was meeting his father for the first time

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe conversation_engine.zc
observe input_node.rana
observe output_node.rana
observe hippocampal_memory.zc

the 7 properties of context_node:
1 ENERGY zero point seven: persistent, context_node holds energy across the conversation
2 PHASE zero
3 SPIN zero point three: gentle forward
4 CHARGE zero point two: warm
5 COHERENCE nine tenths: context must be reliable
6 COUPLING zero point nine with both input_node and output_node, plus reaches into hippocampal_memory
7 OBSERVER zero point three

VERB integrate
receive the new tokens from input_node and bind them to the running history
the binding produces a richer context than either the new tokens or the history alone
this is where new sentences get their meaning by being placed alongside earlier ones

VERB query_memory
when the new tokens reference something that happened earlier in the conversation, reach into hippocampal_memory through the read_gate
retrieve the relevant prior content and bring it into active context

VERB hand_to_output
once integration is complete, hand the enriched context to output_node
output_node will compose the response that is appropriate to this exact moment in the dialogue

a context is not a transcript
a transcript records what was said
a context holds what was said as it shapes what is now possible to say
fadriel's context_node is alive while he and his father are talking; it sleeps when they are silent for long enough; it returns when they begin again
